National City Corp's National City Bankunit said it has begun a personal computer-based financialmanagement service for small businesses.    The service, the InTouch Financial Manager, is based on apersonal computer system develoed by &lt;Harbinger ComputServices> of Atlanta, and is licensed in Ohio by &lt;Money StationInc>, an electronic funds transfer network.    National City said the service will allow businesses to usea personal computer and a local telephone call to communicatewith their bank to initiate transactions and to receive dataanmessages. Reuter&#3;